.TH FETCHX 1 "March 2026" "FetchX 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
fetchx \- A blazing-fast system information tool written in Rust
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBfetchx\fR [OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
FetchX is a modern neofetch replacement written in Rust. It displays system information with ASCII art or images in the terminal.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-b, --backend\fR <BACKEND>
Image backend: ascii, kitty, sixel, chafa, w3m, iterm2, off
.TP
\fB\-s, --source\fR <SOURCE>
Image source: auto, ascii, wallpaper
.TP
\fB--ascii-distro\fR <DISTRO>
Which distro's ASCII art to display
.TP
\fB\-\-emoji\fR
Use emoji mode
.TP
\fB\-\-nerd-font\fR
Use Nerd Font icons for labels
.TP
\fB\-c, --custom-image\fR <PATH>
Path to custom image
.TP
\fB\-l, --logo-only\fR
Only show the logo, no info
.TP
\fB--json\fR
Print output as JSON
.TP
\fB--no-color\fR
Disable colors in output
.TP
\fB--stdout\fR
Disable formatting (for piping)
.TP
\fB--create-config\fR
Create default config file
.TP
\fB--show-config\fR
Show config file path
.TP
\fB--print-config\fR
Print default config to stdout
.TP
\fB--select-image\fR
Interactive image selector
.TP
\fB--init-api-image\fR
Quick setup: enable kitty + API images
.TP
\fB--daemon\fR
Run as background daemon
.TP
\fB--tray-status\fR
Compact status for tray widgets
.TP
\fB\-h, --help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V, --version\fR
Print version
.SH CONFIGURATION
Config file is located at: ~/.config/fetchx/config.toml
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic usage:
$ fetchx
.TP
With kitty image:
$ fetchx --backend kitty
.TP
JSON output:
$ fetchx --json
